15,01You hunt through,
15,01the corridors,
15,01the trials,
15,01the roads,
15,01everywhere.

15,01You draw forth the beast within,
15,01us all.
15,01You seek the jugular of life,
15,01of birth,
15,01of death.

15,01You enchant,
15,01You capture,
15,01You posse your prey.

15,01You kill,
15,01all reason,
15,01all though,
15,01all self control.

15,01You force your victim
15,01to love it,
15,01desire it,
15,01lust it.

15,01You retreat
15,01your victim in despair.
15,01You abandon him,
15,01but leave behind the seeds
15,01of want.
15,01The seeds of need.

15,01You wait,
15,01impatient for,
